<TABLE WIDTH="600" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

<!-- * ROW 1 * -->
	<TR VALIGN="top">

	<!-- COLUMN 1:  LEFT TEXT PROMOS -->
		<TD WIDTH="290">

		<BR>

		<STRONG>Power of 10 Supports Schools.</STRONG> The Apple <A HREF="http://www.education.apple.com/education/power10/index.html">Power of 10</A> program encourages communities to "earn together and learn together" by crediting 10% of the price of each computer to a non-profit K-12 school in the U.S.<BR>

		<BR>

		<STRONG>Add-on Take-off Rebates.</STRONG> Higher Ed customers can get mail-in <a href="http://hed.info.apple.com/Pages/promo.html">rebates</a> when they buy Power Mac (including 6500 series) and PowerBook systems, LaserWriter printers, QuickTake cameras, scanners or displays.<BR>

		<BR>

		<STRONG>Mac 5400 + Bonus Software.</STRONG> The Power Macintosh 5400/180 offers a <A HREF="http://ed.info.apple.com/education/events/aene/pm5400promo.html">special bonus</A> for education. K-12 educational institutions will receive a free bonus software kit.<BR>

		
		<BR>

<!-- note: CyberSurfari expires Nov. 21 -->
		<strong>Exploring Cyberspace.</strong> A treasure hunt designed to help individuals, families and school teams learn about and enjoy the World Wide Web, <a href="http://www.spa.org/cybersurfari/">CyberSurfari '97</a> challenges you to find treasures located at each of 110 cyberspace outposts.<BR>

		
		<BR>
		
		
		<STRONG>Take Good Care of Yourself.</STRONG> Ban the burgers, can the chips, eat less meat, take more walks. The K-12 curriculum Theme of the Month gathers Internet resources about <A HREF="http://ed.info.apple.com/education/techlearn/ccenter/nhpe/nhpemenu.html">Nutrition, Health and Physical Education.</A><BR>



		</TD>

	<!-- COLUMN 2: CENTER GUTTER -->
		<TD WIDTH="20">
		<IMG SRC="/main/elements/spacer.gif" WIDTH="7" HEIGHT="1" ALT=""></TD>

	<!-- COLUMN 3: RIGHT TEXT PROMOS -->
		<TD WIDTH="290">

		<BR>
		
<STRONG>Computers in School.</STRONG> An <A HREF="http://ed.info.apple.com/education/lswtf/idc/index.html">IDC study</A> of the costs and values of K-12 educational computing in America reveals that schools whose computing platform is mostly Mac use more applications and report the most positive results among students and teachers.<BR>

		<BR>
			
		<STRONG>Meeting Place.</STRONG> The <A HREF="http://hed.info.apple.com/"> Learning Community Connection</A> offers a place where Higher Ed customers can meet to find out how Apple products and technologies can help institutions enhance learning opportunities and advance educational innovations.<BR>

		<BR>

		<strong>K-12 Resource Guide.</strong> The November issue of the <a href="http://ed.info.apple.com/education/aerg/">Apple Education Resource Guide</a> surveys products, programs and solutions for K-12 customers from Apple. In addition to an overview, you'll find news about Apple's newest computers, the G3 <a href="http://ed.info.apple.com/education/products/g3series.html">desktop and minitower</a> and the <a href="http://ed.info.apple.com/education/products/pbg3.html">PowerBook G3</a>.<br>

		<BR>
		

	    <STRONG>Buyer Bonuses.</STRONG> K-12 institutions that purchase two eMate 300 8-packs can receive a bonus <A HREF="http://education.apple.com/education/promos/emate-cart.html">eMate 300 storage cart</A> or two <A HREF="http://education.apple.com/education/promos/emate-cart2.html">8-packs of Author's Toolkit</A> software. Institutions that buy a <A HREF="http://education.apple.com/education/promos/webkit-5pk.html">5-pack of Apple Web Page Construction Kits</A> enjoy a saving of almost 40%.<BR>

		
		
		</TD>
	</TR>

